cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a solution to reduce the amount of data exchanged in backhaul and fronthaul links in C-RANs, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives tractable expressions for effective capacity and energy efficiency performance, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed cluster content caching structure takes full advantages of distributed caching, which is a distributed computing problem. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The joint design of resource allocation and RRH association is optimized, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the improvement of QoS guarantees for real-time services, which are related to multimedia applications.
